questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue in a high-throughput Spring Boot application running on JDK 17 with `G1GC`. After several days of operation, the application crashes with `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace`. You trace the leak to a custom dynamic rule engine service:

java
@Service
public class RuleEngine {
    private final ThreadLocal<MyClassLoader> loaderCache = ThreadLocal.withInitial(() -> 
        new MyClassLoader(Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader())
    );

    public void executeRule(String ruleId, byte[] bytecode) throws Exception {
        MyClassLoader loader = loaderCache.get();
        Class<?> ruleClass = loader.defineClass("Rule_" + ruleId, bytecode);
        Runnable ruleInstance = (Runnable) ruleClass.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();
        ruleInstance.run();
    }
}
